@startuml 3C_Event_Lifecycle_RSVP
title 3-C · Event Lifecycle, RSVP & Reminders (UC-T19 to UC-T22, UC-F20 to UC-F23, UC-S11)

start
|Tenant Admin (Owner/Admin)|
:Open Events > New Event;
:Enter title, description, event type,\nstart/end time, location, ticket URL and visibility;

|System|
:Validate tenant ACTIVE and event data;
if (Event valid?) then (No)
  :Return 422 validation error;
  stop
else (Yes)
  :Create IdolEvent status = UPCOMING;
  :Notify eligible fans if enabled;
endif

|Tenant Admin (Owner/Admin)|
if (Admin action?) then (Update Event)
  :Edit event details or visibility;
  |System|
  :Validate and save event changes;
elseif (Admin action?) then (Cancel Event)
  :Confirm cancellation reason;
  |System|
  :Set event status = CANCELLED;
  :Notify fans with RSVP if enabled;
else (View Attendance Report)
  |System|
  :Aggregate RSVP counts and fan list;
  |Tenant Admin (Owner/Admin)|
  :View attendance report;
endif

|Anonymous Visitor / Registered Fan|
:Browse public or subscriber events;

|System|
:Apply event visibility rules;
if (Fan can view event?) then (No)
  :Show locked preview or upgrade prompt;
  stop
else (Yes)
  :Render event detail;
endif

|Registered Fan|
if (Fan action?) then (RSVP)
  :Select GOING, INTERESTED or NOT_GOING;
elseif (Fan action?) then (Change RSVP)
  :Choose a new RSVP status;
else (No RSVP)
  stop
endif

|System|
:Require logged-in fan;
:Create or update EventRsvp\n(unique event_id + fan_id);
:Return updated RSVP counts;

|Scheduled Job Runner|
:Run Send Event Reminders job before event time;
|System|
:Deliver in-app/email reminders to eligible fans;
stop
@enduml
